sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K101004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Construct of LacI promoter, RBS, p22 mnt gene, terminator
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: In this part a LacI promoter is attached to a medium strength RBS which is used to produce p22 mnt protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jeremiah Riesberg
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: A medium strength RBS was used to match other pieces of the project.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This is a composite we put together from existing Biobrick parts.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mnt (s)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: mnt repressor (strong) from Salmonella phage P22 (+LVA)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: crackdots
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
wild type dimeric repressor from enterobacteriophage p22 with dissociation constant of 2.5*10^-12.

sequence was translated with the E.Coli K12 codon usage table, and nucleotides 95-97 was changed from AAT to AAC to avoid the cut site GAATTC (94-99).

Identification of Functionally Important Residues in the DNA Binding Region of the MNT Repressor
Kendall, KL; Sauer, RT
The Journal of Biological Chemistry, 264(23):13706-13710, 1989

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: LacI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Inverting regulatory region controlled by LacI (BBa_C0010, BBa_C0011, etc.)

The pLac regulatory region is a 243 base-pair sequence with standard BioBrick prefix and suffix sections on its ends. It contains two protein binding sites: CAP, which is generally present in E.coli and is assocciated with cell health and availability of glucose., and LacI, the Lac inhibitor BBa_C0010 which binds in an dimerized cooperative manner to inhibit the transcription of the protein that follows. In the presence of lactose or IPTG, an analog of lactose, LacI is unable to correctly bind and inhibit transcription. This allows BBa_R0010 to be used as a inverter or as a detector of lactose or IPTG.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The Plac insert was PCR'd from the MG1655 strain of E.coli K12.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: LacI binds to this regulator. This part is incompatible with species containing active LacI coding regions. Lactose and IPTG disable the operation of LacI and this regulator. This part is incompatible with environments containing lactose or lactose analogs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B1006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Artificial terminator, estimated %T~>90% *8bp stem, 6nt loop *Bidirectional, estimated reverse %T~>90%
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Haiyao Huang
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: modified E. coli thr terminator, replaced all A-T pairs in stem with C-G pairs
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Bidirectional, with the reverse estimated to be less effective than the forward. Has a polyA tail of 9 residues.
